<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<cfsSimulation xmlns="http://www.cfs++.org/simulation" 
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.cfs++.org/simulation 
https://opencfs.gitlab.io/cfs/xml/CFS-Simulation/CFS.xsd">
 
  <documentation>
    <title>Anisotropic Feature Mapping, Single Feature</title>
    <authors>
      <author>Fabian Wein</author>
    </authors>
    <date>2025-10-13</date>
    <references>no</references>
    <isVerified>no</isVerified>
    <description>
      This is the anisotropic variant of feature mapping. Here with a single oriented pill. 
      In contrast to Greifenstein et al., Efficient spline design via feature-mapping for continuous fiber-reinforced structures, 2023
      we have a another anisotropic modeling, we have the full featuere the same orientation

      From the orientation of the feature, the region material is rotated. 

      This is the single case:
      c_e = R*rho_e*c_0*R^T = rho_e * R*c_0*R^T where rho_e=rho_e(s) and R=R(s) with variables s
      
      We actually always have the multi features case (see the aniso_two test) but for one feature it breaks down to the above form 

      While standard feature mapping only has gradient where rho_e is not constant (within transition zone of boundary),
      we have a angle derivate everywhere, where rho_e is not 0. Therefore we prefer to use the ground material approach,
      where we add a constant void everywhere and can rho_min allow to be 0.
    </description>
  </documentation>

  <fileFormats>
    <input>
      <hdf5 fileName="aniso_single.h5ref"/>
    </input>
    <output>
      <hdf5/>
      <info/>
    </output>
    <materialData file="mat.xml" format="xml"/>
  </fileFormats>

  <domain geometryType="plane">
    <regionList>
      <!-- we use the same material as for the anisotropic spaghetti tests. E_x = 1, E_y = 0.1 -->
      <region name="mech" material="spaghetti_aniso"/>
    </regionList>
    <nodeList>
      <nodes name="load">
        <coord x="1" y="0.5"/>
      </nodes>
    </nodeList>
  </domain>

  <sequenceStep index="1">
    <analysis>
      <static/>
    </analysis>

    <pdeList>
      <mechanic subType="planeStrain">
        <regionList>
          <region name="mech"/>
        </regionList>

        <bcsAndLoads>
           <fix name="left"> 
              <comp dof="x"/> 
              <comp dof="y"/> 
           </fix>
           <force name="load" >
             <comp dof="x" value="1"/>
           </force>
        </bcsAndLoads>
        <storeResults>
          <elemResult type="mechPseudoDensity">
            <allRegions/>
          </elemResult>
          <elemResult type="mechTensor">
            <allRegions />
          </elemResult>
          <nodeResult type="mechDisplacement">
            <allRegions/>
          </nodeResult>
        </storeResults>
      </mechanic>
    </pdeList>
    
    <!-- <linearSystems>
      <system>
        <solverList>
          <cholmod/>
        </solverList>
      </system>
    </linearSystems> -->
  </sequenceStep>
    
  <optimization>
    <costFunction type="compliance" task="minimize" sequence="1" linear="false">
      <stopping queue="2" value="1e-3" type="relativeCostChange" />
    </costFunction>

    <constraint type="volume" bound="upperBound" value="0.3" mode="constraint" linear="false"/>

    <optimizer type="snopt" maxIterations="30" >
      <snopt iteration="major">
        <option name="major_optimality_tolerance" type="real" value="1e-6"/>
        <option type="integer" name="verify_level" value="-1"/>
      </snopt>
    </optimizer>
    
    <!-- featureMappingAniso for rotating the region material by the pill orientation.
         Otherwise the region material is just scaled, not rotated.-->
    <ersatzMaterial region="mech" material="mechanic" method="featureMappingAniso">
      <featureMapping transition=".1" order="3" combine="max" >
        <pill>
          <node dof="x" initial="0.1" upper="1" lower="0" tip="start"/>
          <node dof="y" initial="0.2" upper="1" lower="0" tip="start"/>
          <node dof="x" initial="0.9" upper="1" lower="0" tip="end"/>
          <node dof="y" initial="0.7" upper="1" lower="0" tip="end"/>
          <profile initial="0.1" lower="0.05" upper=".2" />
        </pill>
      </featureMapping>
      <!-- Initial is ignored. Groundmaterial speeds up in the anisotropic case -->
      <design name="density" initial=".5" physical_lower="0" upper="1.0" groundmaterial="void" />

      <transferFunction type="identity" application="mech" />
      <export save="all" write="iteration"/>
      
    </ersatzMaterial>
    <commit mode="forward" stride="1"/>
  </optimization>
</cfsSimulation>
